You cannot sent out emails trying to convince people to send you money by stating that your child is dying from cancer. The following are violations of the Can-Spam Act of 2003:
1. Using deceptive subject lines; 
2. Sending bulk messages without recipient's permission; 
3. Forging email headers to hide identity; 
4. Including misleading or false information in messages; 
5. Not including opt-out information in messages; and 
6. Not including valid physical address. Moreover, such emails are unethical, cruel, and insensitive.
